article.headline: Pacific 70, CS Northridge 66
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Mike Webb scored 23 points, including two key free throws in the closing seconds, as Pacific beat Cal State Northridge 70-66 on Saturday. With the win the Tigers (20-7, 10-2) earned a tie for its third consecutive Big West Conference regular-season title. Pacific has won 13 of its last 16 games and will have one of two byes in the conference tournament. The Tigers also were led by Johnny Gray who scored 14 points and Christian Maraker who finished with 12. Northridge (10-15, 3-9), losers of seven of nine, got 17 points apiece from Johnathan Heard and Mike Efevberha. Pacific led 35-26 at halftime, but Northridge scored the first four points of the second half to cut the lead to five. The Tigers built the lead to as much as nine points before the Matadors went on a 19-8 run to tie the score at 57-57 with 3:23 remaining. But the Tigers responded with two field goals and nine free throws to close out the game.
